## Dependencies (External)
- **Bootstrap 5.1.3:** CDN (jsdelivr), integrity hash in HTML. Used for layout and form controls.
- No npm/node or package manager required for current setup.
- No external APIs.

## Critical Technical Details
- **Canvas dimensions:** 1080×1080 (internal); display is constrained by CSS (`max-width: 100%`, `max-height: 800px` for `#myCanvas`).
- **Text on card:** `context.font = "300 35pt Satorp"`, `context.fillStyle = '#2F388D'`, `context.textAlign = 'center'`. Name position: `canvasWidth / 2`, `canvasHeight - 300`. When adding the chosen message, positions must be defined (e.g. message above or below name).
- **Download:** Filename `moa3aydah.png`; implemented via `<a download>` and `URL.createObjectURL(blob)` from `canvas.toBlob()`.
- **RTL/LTR:** Arabic page uses `dir="rtl"` and Arabic placeholder/labels; English uses `dir="ltr"` and English labels. Canvas text alignment may need to account for RTL when drawing Arabic (e.g. `direction` or positioning).

## Development Environment
- Static file server or open-in-browser is sufficient (e.g. `file://` or any static host).
- No build, transpilation, or bundling in current setup.
- Browsers: Standard modern browsers with Canvas and Blob support (desktop and mobile).

## Constraints
- No server-side logic; all state is in the current page (and, when implemented, in JS variables for chosen language and chosen message).
- Asset paths in JS are relative to the HTML file (e.g. `assets/images/...`, `assets/fonts/...`). Keep this consistent when adding new assets.
